{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"747ecfe5-65a1-491d-a68f-9f0e09acda34","content":"This is a known **behavioral difference** between VSTest and MTP.\n\n**The problem:** MTP returns **exit code 8** (\"no tests discovered\") when an assembly yields zero tests. VSTest silently returned 0 in that scenario. Since your tests are behind `#if INCLUDE_SLOW_TESTS`, builds without that symbol produce an empty test assembly.\n\n**The fix:** Tell MTP to ignore the \"zero tests\" exit code. Add this property to your project (or `Directory.Build.props` for all projects):","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01NkjwoThJxASwZLy8US3B5u","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-c9d3a7d9743743699c48620354eb4bfc/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n    <!-- Treat 'no tests discovered' (exit code 8) as success, matching VSTest behavior.\n         Required for configurations where conditional compilation excludes all tests. -->\n    <TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>--ignore-exit-code 8</TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-c9d3a7d9743743699c48620354eb4bfc/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"099d6c7f-7a56-43aa-a0fe-5f9462b5aab7","outputTokens":394,"requestId":"480C:12EB87:5C8E46C:6410CCE:69FBE3CF"},"id":"41abe593-7ce7-4c79-acba-e8fc3a3ea51e","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:59:03.027Z","parentId":"27ea8369-aa07-4de4-ba52-ffa8643bb103"}
