{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"21aca46b-1004-4698-85c7-a163124a00f5","content":"Both scenarios now exit with **0**. Here's a summary:\n\n### What changed\n\nAdded `--ignore-exit-code 8` via `<TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>` in the csproj. This tells MTP to treat \"no tests discovered\" as success — matching the old VSTest behavior.\n\n### Why exit code 8?\n\nMTP intentionally returns non-zero when zero tests are found (to catch misconfiguration). VSTest returned 0. For assemblies that legitimately have zero tests due to conditional compilation, `--ignore-exit-code 8` is the correct opt-in.\n\n**Tip:** If you have many test projects, put this property in a shared `Directory.Build.props` instead.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"099d6c7f-7a56-43aa-a0fe-5f9462b5aab7","outputTokens":167,"requestId":"4840:112B3A:2F2F795:33D3DAD:69FBE3DE"},"id":"adb7ed38-8e32-4e4b-b155-a86ac207542a","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:59:18.205Z","parentId":"2f2317d9-3fa1-412a-9284-2342643b8fad"}
